section.section:
Each nutrient management plan shall be developed considering factors including:
Levels of bioavailable nitrogen and phosphorus in the soil;
Levels of bioavailable nitrogen and phosphorus in all fertilizer materials to be applied;
The amount of nitrogen and phosphorus necessary to achieve the expected crop yield for the land that is the subject of the nutrient management plan, as determined by:
Soil erodibility and nutrient retention capacity;
Existing best management practices.
